@startuml
title Refactoring: From Tight Coupling to Decoupled Adapter

' --- Scenario 1: Tight Coupling (Anti-Pattern) ---
participant "High-Level Module\n(Client)" as Client
participant "Low-Level Module\n(Adaptee)" as Legacy

box "Problem: Tight Coupling" #LightCoral
    participant Client
    participant Legacy
end box

note over Client, Legacy: **BEFORE REFACTORING**
Client -> Legacy : specificRequest()\n<color:red><b>Client knows internal details!</b></color>
activate Legacy
Legacy --> Client : data
deactivate Legacy

' --- Divider ---
== Refactoring Intervention ==

' --- Scenario 2: Decoupled (Adapter Pattern) ---
participant "High-Level Module\n(Client)" as Client_New
participant "Target Interface" as Interface
participant "Adapter" as Adapter
participant "Low-Level Module\n(Adaptee)" as Legacy_New

box "Solution: Decoupled Adapter" #LightGreen
    participant Client_New
    participant Interface
    participant Adapter
    participant Legacy_New
end box

note over Client_New, Legacy_New: **AFTER REFACTORING**

Client_New -> Interface : request()\n<color:green><b>Client speaks generic language</b></color>
activate Interface

Interface -> Adapter : request()
activate Adapter

note right of Adapter : **Translation Layer**\nConverts generic request\nto specific call
Adapter -> Legacy_New : specificRequest()
activate Legacy_New

Legacy_New --> Adapter : data
deactivate Legacy_New

Adapter --> Interface : data
deactivate Adapter

Interface --> Client_New : data
deactivate Interface

@enduml